# Lodestar — Session Context for Cursor

This project uses Lodestar for session context management. A `.lodestar.md` file in the project root contains decisions, patterns, and open questions from previous coding sessions.

## At the start of every session
Call `lodestar_load` with projectRoot set to the workspace root. Read the returned context to understand what was decided, what patterns are established, and where the previous session left off.

## At the end of every session
Call `lodestar_synthesize` with projectRoot set to the workspace root. Include any notes the user mentions about what they worked on in the sessionNotes parameter.

## During the session
If the user says "lodestar save" or "save checkpoint", call `lodestar_synthesize` to capture mid-session progress.

## Key commands the user may say
- "lodestar start" or "load context" → call lodestar_load
- "lodestar save" or "save session" → call lodestar_synthesize
- "lodestar end" or "end session" → call lodestar_synthesize
- "what did we work on last" → call lodestar_load and summarize

## Important
- Always use the workspace root as projectRoot
- The .lodestar.md file is committed to git — it's part of the project
- Don't modify .lodestar.md directly — only Lodestar writes to it
